  "helpTitle": "Help & FAQ",
  "helpQCreateMess": "How do I create a mess?",
  "helpACreateMess": "On first launch, choose \"I manage a mess,\" then follow the wizard: name your mess, add members from your contacts or manually, and choose whether meal costs and other bills are tracked together or separately.",
  "helpQAddMembers": "How do I add or remove members later?",
  "helpAAddMembers": "Open Members from the drawer. Tap \"Add from contacts\" or \"Add manually\" to add someone. To remove someone, use the ⋮ menu on their row — Deactivate keeps their history, Delete member only works if they have no meals, expenses, or payments recorded yet.",
  "helpQRoles": "What do roles and permissions mean?",
  "helpARoles": "The App Admin (the mess creator) always has full access. Every other member can be a Sub-Admin with only the permissions you choose (e.g. managing meals but not money), or a plain Member who can view everything but not edit. Set this up from Roles & permissions.",
  "helpQJoin": "How does a member join from their own phone?",
  "helpAJoin": "First bring your mess online (Settings → Mess → Online) to get an invite code. Share that code with the member. They open MessBook, choose \"I'm joining a mess,\" sign in with Google, and enter the code — then either claim their existing name or add themselves as new.",
  "helpQMeals": "How do I track meals?",
  "helpAMeals": "Open Meals from the drawer to log each member's meals per day, including half meals and guest meals. You can also set up a weekly routine per member so their usual meals fill in automatically.",
  "helpQMealRate": "How is the meal rate calculated?",
  "helpAMealRate": "The meal rate is the total meal spending for the month divided by the total number of meals everyone ate. Each member's meal bill is their own meal count multiplied by that rate.",
  "helpQPolls": "What are meal polls for?",
  "helpAPolls": "Polls let members vote on which meals they'll take for a given day, instead of the manager guessing or asking everyone individually. Anyone with poll-creation permission can start one; every member can vote regardless of role.",
  "helpQSettleUp": "How does Settle Up work?",
  "helpASettleUp": "Settle Up looks at everyone's balance and suggests the fewest possible payments to bring every balance to zero, instead of everyone paying everyone else individually.",
  "helpQMonthClose": "What happens when I close a month?",
  "helpAMonthClose": "Closing a month locks its meals, expenses, and deposits so they can no longer be edited, and starts a fresh month. You can choose to carry forward each member's balance as an opening entry in the new month.",
  "helpQBackup": "How do I back up my data?",
  "helpABackup": "Go to Backup & restore from the drawer to export a backup file anytime, or import one to restore. This works fully offline and doesn't require an account.",
  "helpQOnline": "Do I need the internet to use MessBook?",
  "helpAOnline": "No — MessBook works fully offline on a single phone. Bringing a mess online (and signing in with Google) is only needed if you want other members to join from their own phones and see live updates.",
